<h4 id="but">But</h4>
<p>there a few way to say but/however, you can’t connect sentence with でも</p>
<ul>
  <li>けれども</li>
  <li>けど</li>
  <li>が</li>
  <li>だが</li>
  <li>しかしながら</li>
</ul>

<ol>
  <li>今日は忙しけど、明日はひまです(casual/more conversational)</li>
  <li>今日は忙しでも、明日は暇だ(wrong)</li>
</ol>

<p>You say something first then start a new sentence with でも, you can start a new sentence with
しかし、だが、but でも is more casual</p>
<ul>
  <li>今日忙しです。でも明日は暇です。</li>
</ul>

<p>####</p>
<ol>
  <li>Add more information to the previous sentence and don’t negate it
    <ul>
      <li>犬が好きです、でも猫が好きです(I like dogs, but I also like cats)</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>When you suggest something, bring up some examples. noun+でも something like
    <ul>
      <li>お茶飲まない</li>
      <li>お茶でも飲まない(It sounds softer and give the listener another choices)</li>
      <li>次の週末、京都にでも行かない</li>
      <li>暇だから、ゲームでもしようかな</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ol>

